From ae57ca56337bbe6286c8323320bb074fa8eb648c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Mon, 15 Jun 2026 14:44:04 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Enforce no-emoji policy; document icon library usage in
 CLAUDE.md

Add rule 6 to the mandatory contribution rules: literal Unicode emoji are
not allowed in the program. Contributors must draw an inline/local SVG or
reuse one of the existing icon libraries instead. Document the icon
resolution order (Semantic UI icons first, then local SVG, then a font an
app already bundles) as a suggestion list.

The convention checker now flags added Unicode emoji as an ERROR across Go
and front-end (HTML/JS/CSS) sources, with a byte-oriented match that avoids
false positives on smart quotes/arrows/check marks and stays portable.
---
 .github/workflows/ci.yml     |  2 +-
 CLAUDE.md                    | 52 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++---
 scripts/check-conventions.sh | 49 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++-------
 3 files changed, 90 insertions(+), 13 deletions(-)

